<refnamediv><indexterm><primary sortas="shut-down-jbi-component">shut-down-jbi-component &mdash; shuts down a service engine or a binding component on the specified target</primary></indexterm><indexterm><primary sortas="shuts down a service engine or a binding component on the specified target">shuts
down a service engine or a binding component on the specified target &mdash; shut-down-jbi-component</primary></indexterm><refname>shut-down-jbi-component</refname><refpurpose>shuts down a service engine or a binding component on the specified target</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>&synp-tt;</title>
<cmdsynopsis><command>shut-down-jbi-component</command>&synopsis-common;
<arg choice="opt">&Dash;&Dash;force=<replaceable>false</replaceable></arg><arg choice="opt">&Dash;&Dash;target <replaceable>target</replaceable></arg><arg choice="plain"><replaceable>component_name</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1><title>&desc-tt;</title>
<para>The <command>shut-down-jbi-component</command> command shuts down a service engine or a binding component on the specified target. If no target is specified, the component will be shut down on the embedded DAS server. </para>
</refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&opts-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="medium">&options-common;
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;F</option> <option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;force</option></term><listitem><para>Setting to true forcibly shuts down the service engine or the binding component. Default is false.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;target</option></term><listitem><para>Specifies the target on which you are shutting down the JBI component. Specify this option only if the JBI component is deployed in a multiserver environment with a Domain Administration Server (DAS). If the JBI
component is not deployed in a multiserver environment with a DAS, this option is ignored. Valid values are:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><literal>server</literal>, which shuts down the service engine or the binding component on the embedded DAS instance. This is the default value.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><literal>domain</literal>, which shuts down the service engine or the binding component on the administrative domain itself. Specify <literal>domain</literal> only if you are using the cluster profile.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><?Pub Caret><para><replaceable>cluster_name</replaceable>, which shuts down the service engine or the binding component for every server instance in the cluster.</para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><replaceable>instance_name</replaceable>, which shuts down the service engine or the binding component for the named unclustered server instance.</para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist></para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&oper-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="medium">
<varlistentry><term><replaceable>component_name</replaceable></term><listitem><para>The name of the binding component or the service engine that you want to shut down.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&exam-tt;</title>
<example>
<title>Using the shut-down-jbi-component command</title>
<para>The following command shuts down a JBI component.</para>
<screen>asadmin> <userinput>shut-down-jbi-component --user admin2
--passwordfile passwords.txt --target NewServer MyWebApp</userinput>
Command shut-down-jbi-component executed successfully.</screen>
</example>
</refsect1>
